# Convert Aibel Builders Static Site → WordPress Theme

The existing site is a static HTML/CSS/JS website for **Aibel Builders**. The goal is to convert it into a self-contained WordPress theme so that admin users can manage **Projects** (including gallery images) and **Career listings** through the standard WordPress dashboard — no code editing required.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This conversion produces a **WordPress theme folder** (`aibel-builders-theme/`). To use it you need a WordPress installation (local via LocalWP/WAMP, or a hosting server with WordPress). The theme includes **no plugins** — it registers its own Custom Post Types (CPTs) and meta boxes using pure PHP, so it works out-of-the-box on a bare WordPress install.

> [!WARNING]
> Your existing GitHub Pages static site will remain untouched. The new `/aibel-builders-theme/` folder must be uploaded to your WordPress server's `wp-content/themes/` directory.

